class FarmSimulation {
  private int rainfall;
  private boolean fertilizerApplied;
  private int cropYield;

  public FarmSimulation(int rainfall) {
    this.rainfall = rainfall;
    this.fertilizerApplied = false;
    this.cropYield = 0;
  }

  public void applyFertilizer() {
    this.fertilizerApplied = true;
  }

  public void calculateCropYield() {
    if (rainfall > 50 && fertilizerApplied) {
      cropYield = 100;
    } else if (rainfall > 50) {
      cropYield = 80;
    } else if (fertilizerApplied) {
      cropYield = 60;
    } else {
      cropYield = 30;
    }
  }

  public int getCropYield() {
    return cropYield;
  }
}",

If we intervene and apply fertilizer, while it rained more than 50mm, will the crop yield necessarily be 100?
